This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the parameter learning of Sum-Product Networks (SPNs) using Expectation-Maximization (EM). It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as SPNs are a type of probabilistic graphical model used for reasoning under uncertainty. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as SPNs are a type of data structure used for probabilistic inference. The paper also mentions experiments on benchmark datasets, which suggests it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.CL (Computation and Language) if the datasets are related to these fields.
